com.hr.expr.example

Class Example

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hr.expr.example.Example

  • public class Example
extends java.lang.Object
    A simple example of parsing and evaluating an expression. This puts the expression evaluator through its paces.

    Sample usage:

    $ java expr.Example '3.14159 * x^2' 0 4 1
    0
    3.14159
    12.5664
    28.2743
    50.2654

    $ java expr.Example 'sin (pi/4 * x)' 0 4 1
    0
    0.707107
    1
    0.707107
    1.22461e-16

    $ java expr.Example 'sin (pi/4 x)' 0 4 1
    I don't understand your formula "sin (pi/4 x)".

    I got as far as "sin (pi/4" and then saw "x".
    I expected ")" at that point, instead.
    An example of a formula I can parse is "sin (pi/4 + x)".
